          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>One parchment folio; Unknown shelfmark; Script style: kūfī kūfī D; Estimated date of production: 9th-10th century; Lines per page: 15; Dimensions: probably ca. 290 x ca. 380 mm (probable dimensions as other folios from the blue Qurʾān); Qurʾānic text: Q 29:51-56 (for the text of the page on display, the text of the backside is unknown).</p>
              <p>An image of this page of the Blue Qurʾān preserved by Bahrain's House of the Qurʾān is accessible in the <ref target="https://ar.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%AA_%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%B1%D8%A2%D9%86">Arabic Wikipedia Entry</ref> of the Museum. Shelfmark and backside of this fragment are unknown (for technical reasons it is listed in this catalogue as fol. 1r), as no catalogue of this important collection is accessible. For a detailed catalogue entry about the Blue Qurʾān, including a large list of sister fragments scattered in collections around the world, see entry <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/2/vers/286?handschrift=1458">HC.MS.03223</ref> (written by Marcus Fraser).</p>
            </summary>
